## Plan: Add Pagination to `GET /users`

### Codebase summary
- **15 users** in `src/data.ts`
- **`src/routes.ts`** — only file with business logic to change
- **`tests/routes.test.ts`** — tests are **already written** and fully specify the expected behavior (4 pagination tests + 2 existing single-user tests)

---

### Two files to touch

**`src/types.ts`** — add a generic response envelope type:
```typescript
export interface PaginatedResponse<T> {
  data: T[];
  pagination: { page: number; limit: number; total: number; totalPages: number; };
}
```

**`src/routes.ts`** — replace the `GET /users` handler:
```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page  = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page  as string, 10) || 1);
  const limit = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10);

  const total      = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const start      = (page - 1) * limit;
  const data       = users.slice(start, start + limit); // [] for out-of-range page

  res.json({ data, pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages } });
});
```

The `GET /users/:id` handler is **not touched**.

---

### Why this satisfies all tests

| Test | Params | Result |
|---|---|---|
| Default | _(none)_ | page=1, limit=10, 10 users, total=15, totalPages=2 |
| Second page | `?page=2&limit=10` | 5 users (11–15) |
| Custom limit | `?limit=5` | 5 users, totalPages=3 |
| Out-of-range | `?page=100` | `data: []`, status 200 |
| Single user | `/users/1` | unchanged ✓ |
| 404 | `/users/999` | unchanged ✓ |

**Verify** with `npm test` — all 6 tests should pass.
